        <div n="662-37L1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">P<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">OOR</hi></hi> ladies! tho' their <hi rend="underline">bus'ness</hi> be to <hi rend="underline">play</hi>,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-line-2"> 'Tis hard they must be busy <hi rend="underline">night</hi> and <hi rend="underline">day</hi>:</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-line-3"> Why shou'd they want the privilege of men,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-line-4"> And take some small <hi rend="underline">diversions</hi>, now and then?</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-line-5"> Had women been the makers of our laws,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-line-6"> (And why they were not, I can see no cause)</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-line-7"> The men shou'd <hi rend="underline">slave</hi> at <hi rend="underline">cards</hi> from morn to night,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-662-37L1-line-8"> And female pleasure be to <hi rend="underline">read</hi> and <hi rend="underline">write</hi>.662-37L1   </l></lg></div>
